# CODEOWNERS — the human-review boundary (Layer 5 of the AI-CTO system)
#
# Purpose: force a NAMED HUMAN review on the highest-risk paths so that AI /
# automation can never silently merge a change to money movement, decisioning,
# PII/KYC, intake/credit policy, schema, consent, secrets, or CI itself. With
# branch protection's "require review from Code Owners" enabled, a PR touching
# any path below cannot merge until the listed owner approves.
#
# See docs/ai_cto/escalation_boundary.md for WHY these are the lines that must
# stay human, and docs/ai_cto/ai_cto_system.md for how this fits the 5 layers.
#
# NOTE: @dmdwebster-collab is a PLACEHOLDER for the repo owner. Replace it (and
# add per-domain reviewers) with the REAL GitHub handles before relying on this:
#   - PRIVACY / COMPLIANCE accountable person (PIPEDA) — the domain co-founder
#   - TECHNICAL owner of record — the founder-engineer
# A team handle (e.g. @org/critical-reviewers) is preferable to an individual
# once a team exists, so review isn't bottlenecked on one person being available.

# --- Money path + APR / cost-of-borrowing cap --------------------------------
/app/services/loan_servicing.py   @dmdwebster-collab
/app/services/loan_lifecycle.py   @dmdwebster-collab
/app/services/loan_quote.py       @dmdwebster-collab

# --- Decisioning engine (flow / credit logic) --------------------------------
/app/services/flow_orchestrator.py   @dmdwebster-collab
/app/services/flow_engine.py         @dmdwebster-collab

# --- PII / KYC (SIN crypto, manual application intake, document handling) -----
/app/core/sin_crypto.py                                  @dmdwebster-collab
/app/api/applicant/v1/endpoints/manual_application.py    @dmdwebster-collab
/app/api/applicant/v1/endpoints/documents.py             @dmdwebster-collab

# --- Intake + product / credit policy ----------------------------------------
/app/api/v1/endpoints/widget_intake.py     @dmdwebster-collab
/app/api/v1/endpoints/credit_products.py   @dmdwebster-collab

# --- Schema (migrations), consent text, secrets/config, and CI itself --------
